              <h3><a name="reading"></a>Summer Reading Challenge begins at Sanderstead Library, 11th July</h3>
              <p>Children can join the National Summer Reading Challenge at any Croydon library, from Saturday 11th July, and take part all summer until 12th September, winning stickers and other prizes. All who read 6 books will get a medal and certificate.</p>
              <p><li>Other events at the library this summer: Dr Seuss Activity, Tuesday 21st July, 3.00-4.00pm.</li>
                <li>Planting activity with stories and crafts for national allotments week, Tuesday 4th August, 3.00-4.00pm.</li>
                <li>Jack and the Beanstalk stories and crafts, Tuesday 25th August, 3.00-4.00pm.</li></p>
              <p>All activities are for children aged 3+. Please reserve a free place at the library. 020 3700 1015,  <%= mail_to "croydon.sandersteadlibrary@carillionservices.co.uk" %></p>
              <p>Wednesday Rhymetimes, 10.30-11.00am and Wiggle and Jiggles, 11.30-12 noon will take place all summer. Wednesday storytime will not take place from the week beginning 20th July. It wil start again in the week beginning 31st August.</p>
            </div><!-- col-md-10 -->
